headline: The Big Companies Funding Trump’s Inauguration Despite Denouncing Jan. 6
summary: Now, many of those companies are lining up to fund  Donald Trump’s  inauguration.  The Wall Street Journal has identified at least 11 companies and trade associations that are backing the inauguration, which is on track to be the most lucrative ever, after earlier pledging to suspend or reconsider political-action committee donations after Jan. 6.  Ford,  Intuit Toyota  and the Pharmaceutical Research and Manufacturers of America are each giving $1 million.
